<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,654,1041]" box="[151,1073,654,682]" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,654,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (including tegmina), male: 
<quantity box="[753,884,654,681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="399" unit="mm" value="5.35" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="5.2">5.2–5.5mm</quantity>
; female: 
<quantity box="[986,1069,654,681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="399" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,654,1041]" box="[199,541,691,717]" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">
Colour as in 
<taxonomicName box="[343,534,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnifacialis">
<emphasis box="[343,363,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[377,534,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">brunnifacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,654,1041]" box="[199,1199,727,753]" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">
Male genitalia similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[481,672,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnifacialis">
<emphasis box="[481,501,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[515,672,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">brunnifacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but style lateral lobe more produced (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1186,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1626,1650]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,278,1594]" captionTargetId="figure-52@19.[151,1436,272,1603]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia and female pregenital sternite of H. quadripicta species group. A–D, H. quadripicta; A, valve and subgenital plate, dorsal view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style; D, female pregenital sternite; E–H, H. sandakanensis; E, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; F, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; G, style; H, female pregenital sternite; I–L, H. singaporensis; I, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; J, aedeagus, caudal view; K, style; L, female pregenital sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4629118/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,654,1041]" box="[199,1066,763,789]" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">
Female pregenital sternite with posterior margin conically rounded (
<figureCitation box="[963,1053,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1626,1650]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,278,1594]" captionTargetId="figure-52@19.[151,1436,272,1603]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia and female pregenital sternite of H. quadripicta species group. A–D, H. quadripicta; A, valve and subgenital plate, dorsal view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style; D, female pregenital sternite; E–H, H. sandakanensis; E, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; F, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; G, style; H, female pregenital sternite; I–L, H. singaporensis; I, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; J, aedeagus, caudal view; K, style; L, female pregenital sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4629118/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="399">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
